I feel bad even posting this because of so much discourse around not feeling bad about new year (which is very important), but just I have to take a moment to celebrate and say that 2022 has been the best year of my life. ✨

Took a huge step in my career well out of my comfort zone, worked hard on something super exciting (and secret - announcement in the new year! 🤩) bought a house, been to see so many bands, attended tons of festivals, made some proper friends for the first time in years, and another year of being with my lovely Andy.

But perhaps the biggest thing is that I have never felt more confident and secured in myself and who I am. I still have miles to go but it’s like a switch was flipped in my head this year and I finally feel content with who I am. 🍾

As someone who spent most of her life as a miserable and anxious puddle, so much work, learning, experience and trial and error has gone into everything to make me this happy and I’m really proud.

I hope everyone has a great new year and is proud of everything they have achieved, big or small :) 

And 2023… Honestly, bring it ON! 🎉

Soooo I wrote a book! 📗 Oaken Tongue is a short story collection imbued with the magic of traditional folk tales, centred on the theme of returning to nature and a warning of what just might happen if we stray too far from it… 🍂 it’s a little bit dark, very much weird, and inspired by my love of folklore and mythology. 🌿

My book (and other magickal items - like this tea!) will launch on my new online shop, Leodrune Shoppe, on the 19th March 🎉 If you’re interested, feel free to follow my writing account @lunaleodrune and @ataleoftwoteas which is the account that will soon transition into Leodrune Shoppe.

Hello! ✨ I am once again doing what everyone told me not to and merging my two accounts. I’ll make a few more posts on here then will be moving forever to @lunaleodrune 🍃

It’s just social media and it’s not a big deal but over the years I’ve put a lot of work into building my account so I wanted to let you know in case you wanted to stay in touch. 

I’m no longer interested in trying to grow on Instagram and just want one, simple account where I can post whatever I want whenever I want, even if it doesn’t fit an ‘aesthetic’. I’m a heavy metal hippie, always have been and always will be, and life is not lived to be one single aesthetic or niche. It’s draining to keep up with and if people don’t like it, they don’t have to follow. 🍄

I’ll be posting whatever I feel like and the things I get up to on @lunaleodrune and on my shop account @leodruneshoppe it will be more curated. 

I am grateful for the community and friends I have made on here, that’s the only important thing. If you’ve stuck with me all this time, thank you! 🖤🌞
